==Starting Out==
===Vanstrom Klause===
* '''Vanstrom Klause:''' Hello there. The name's Vanstrom Klause. How goes it stranger?
* '''Player:''' Quite well, thanks for asking. How about you?
* '''Vanstrom Klause:''' Hmm, well, I am a little concerned about some friends of mine. They're in dire need of some assistance, but I'm at a loss as to how I can help them.
* '''Player:''' What friends are these?
* '''Vanstrom Klause:''' It's a personal tragedy that I have yet to meet them in the flesh. But their exploits make mouth watering stories... The real meat and drink of high adventure and daring... So they say.
* '''Player:''' What does that mean exactly? I mean, I have some stories. I'm quite a hero myself, you may actually be talking about me?
* '''Vanstrom Klause:''' They're a group of rebels fighting against the vampyres that rule over Morytania. They're known as the Myreque. Some people call them terrorists while others call them freedom fighters!
* '''Player:''' I see. And you want to help them?
* '''Vanstrom Klause:''' Of course. I'm a big fan of their cause. I was hoping to supply them with some new weapons. Alas, I find that I'm rather lacking in ability when it comes to this kind of thing!
* {{tselect|Start the In Search of the Myreque quest?}}
* {{topt|Yes.}}
** '''Player:''' Well perhaps I could take these weapons to the Myreque. What do they need?
** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' Really? You would help?
** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' I was hoping to deliver some steel to them. A longsword, two shortswords, a dagger, a mace and a warhammer.
** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' Though if you wish to do this, I'm afraid you'll need to acquire the weapons yourself. My efforts to procure them have been rather unsuccessful.
** '''Player:''' Right. Get some steel weapons and take them to the Myreque. Where can I find them?
** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' The vampyres are always hunting them, so they keep themselves hidden. I hear the boatman in Mort'ton has dealings with them though.
** '''Player:''' Well I'd better get going then.
** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' How wonderful! Perhaps the people of Morytania now have an additional hero that they can come to rely on?
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|What else do you know about the Myreque?}}
*** '''Player:''' What else do you know about the Myreque?
*** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' There's always some evil heel ready to grind the face of humanity into the dirt. Here in Morytania, it's the vampyres! They rule over the region with an iron fist, killing any who oppose them.
*** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' The Myreque are the only ones brave enough to stand up to them. They stay in the shadows though, lest the vampyres track them down!
*** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' No one knows for sure how many of them there are. The group hiding in Mort Myre supposedly has six members. There are whispers of more in other parts of Morytania though.
*** '''Player:''' And this group in Mort Myre? They're who the weapons are for?
*** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' Yes, indeed! The Myreque are almost certainly able to handle themselves... But they need the tools to do it!
*** (shows other options)
** {{topt|Remind me, what weapons do I need?}}
*** '''Player:''' Remind me, what weapons do I need?
*** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' You've forgotten already? Ha! That's funny! But I do understand, my memory isn't what it was either!
*** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' I'd suggest a longsword, two shortswords, a dagger, a mace and a warhammer, all made of steel.
*** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' You'll need to obtain the weapons yourself. Fear not though! If you return to me here once you've found them, I'll be sure to give you a nice surprise in return for your help!
*** (shows other options)
** {{topt|Where can I find this boatman?}}
*** '''Player:''' Where can I find this boatman?
*** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' I hear he lives in Mort'ton. You'll find the town south of here, through Mort Myre. It's a nasty place, but where isn't in Morytania?
*** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' Most of the town has supposedly fallen to some strange affliction. The boatman is apparently one of the few healthy people left!
*** '''Player:''' And you say he's had dealings with the Myreque?
*** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' So I hear. There are many who sympathise with their movement. Rumour is that this boatman's been ferrying supplies to their hideout, somewhere in Mort Myre!
*** (shows other options)
** {{topt|I'd better be off.}}
*** '''Player:''' I'd better be off.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|No.}}
** '''Player:''' I wish I could help, but I'm busy at the moment.
** '''Vanstrom Klause:''' Oh well, I'm sure someone will be along to help soon. Thanks for even considering it though.
** {{tact|end}}

