==Convincing Cyreg Paddlehorn==
===Talking to Cyreg===
* '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Hello there friend.
* '''Player:''' Hello there. I'm guessing you're the boatman?
* '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Well I am 'a' boatman. I don't know about 'the' boatman though. Why do you ask anyway?
* '''Player:''' I hear you have dealings with the Myreque. I was hoping to take some weapons to them.
* '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Hmm, I'm sure I don't know what you're talking about.
* '''Player:''' Come on, I know you're in cahoots with them. It's important that I get these weapons to them.
* '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Well... Okay, I may have done some work for them before. It's too dangerous now though. I'm sorry, I can't help you.

* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Oh come on, you can tell me!}}
** '''Player:''' Oh come on, you can tell me!
** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' I'm sorry, I just can't... They're watching us you know... Eyes everywhere!
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Well, I guess they'll just die without weapons.}}
** '''Player:''' Well, I guess they'll just die without weapons.
** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Hmm, you don't seem too concerned about their welfare. I'm glad I didn't tell you where they are. In any case, they're resourceful, they can look after themselves.
** '''Player:''' What's that supposed to mean?
** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' They're resourceful folks, that's all I'm saying. The leader of their group, Veliaf, looks after them well.

** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|Oh come on, you can tell me!}}
*** {{tact|above}}
*** {{tact|previous}}
** {{topt|Resourceful enough to get their own steel weapons?}}
*** '''Player:''' Resourceful enough to get their own steel weapons?
*** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Maybe they are... What do you care anyway? They've been up against it ever since they got started.
*** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' All of 'em have suffered more loss and heartache than you'll ever know. Now, leave me be!

*** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
*** {{topt|What have they been up against?}}
**** '''Player:''' What have they been up against?
**** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' You're clearly not from around here or you wouldn't be asking such foolish questions.
**** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Drakan. That's what they've been up against.
**** '''Player:''' Drakan?
**** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Lord Lowerniel Drakan. Leader of the vampyres and ruler of Morytania. His reign over these lands means we all live in fear.
**** {{tact|other}}
*** {{topt|What kind of loss and heartache have they suffered?}}
**** '''Player:''' What kind of loss and heartache have they suffered?
**** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' The worst kind. Most have lost members of their family.
**** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Take Sani Piliu for example. she was orphaned overnight when a vampyre went on the rampage. Imagine that, losing your entire family in one night. Terrible!
**** '''Player:''' It sounds awful... Who is Sani Piliu?
**** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' She's the only female member of the Myreque. Her agility and light fingers have got them out of quite a few sticky situations.
**** {{tact|other}}
*** {{topt|If you don't tell me, their deaths are on your head!}}
**** '''Player:''' If you don't tell me, their deaths are on your head!
**** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' There's death aplenty in this forsaken place... What do I care that some fool hardy vigilantes decided to go it alone against the Drakans?
**** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Stupidity of youth is to blame. I won't carry it on my shoulders!

**** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
**** {{topt|One mans vigilante is another mans freedom fighter!}}
***** '''Player:''' One man's vigilante is another man's freedom fighter!
***** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Aye, you can see it from both sides I suppose. But many of us consider it fool hardy to fight for something we'll never get.
***** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' I remember a conversation I had with Polmafi, a scholar, such as he was. Even he agrees that the chances are slim.
***** '''Player:''' Polmafi? Who's he?
***** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Polmafi Ferdygris is one of the Myreque. He's a technical sort and advises on all sorts of things to Veliaf. He was a scholar before he became a renegade.
***** {{tact|other}}
**** {{topt|What do you know of the Drakans?}}
***** '''Player:''' What do you know of the Drakans?
***** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' They're the family that leads the vampyres. They're the ones to whom the blood tithes are paid. Too much I have told you already!
***** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Ignorance is better than these truths I tell you! I can pretend once more that I am a free man and some relief from this gloom can I feel again.
***** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Be gone with you now and leave me with my dreams.
***** {{tact|other}}
**** {{topt|What kind of a man are you to say that you don't care?}}
***** '''Player:''' What kind of a man are you to say that you don't care?
***** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Don't dare to judge me young fool... what do you know of the heartache I carry? I want to help them! I did help them! But my part is done now. To do any more is to risk death!
***** '''Player:''' You're risking death either way. Better to risk it and help the cause, than to stand by and do nothing.
***** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Hmmm. Very well, if you would take your chance to help these strangers, who am I to stop you?
***** '''Player:''' So you'll help me? Will you take me to them?

***** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' No, I won't take you, but you can use my boat.
***** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' You'll be going through Mort Myre though, so I won't be letting you go unless you've got some defence against the ghasts.
***** {{tcond|If the player does not have a druid pouch in their inventory:}}
****** '''Player:''' I don't have anything which I can use against them.
****** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Well return to me once you have.
****** {{tact|end}}
***** {{tcond|If the player has a [[Druid Pouch]] in their inventory:}}
****** {{tbox|pic=Druid pouch detail.png|You show the boatman your druid pouch.}}
****** '''Player:''' I have this druid pouch! This turns the ghasts visible and I can kill them once I can see them.
****** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Very well, you can go! But you'll need to bring me six wooden planks first.
****** '''Player:''' What for?
****** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' The boat took some damage on my last trip. It needs repairing. There's also a bridge you'll need to cross later in your journey. It's rotten and will likely need repairs.
****** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Three of the planks are for the boat and three are for the bridge. I suggest you bring some tools and steel nails along as well.
****** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
****** {{topt|Here are some planks for you.}}
******* '''Player:''' Here are some planks for you.
******* {{tbox|pic=Plank detail.png|The boatman takes three wooden planks from you and uses them to fix his boat.}}
******* '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Right. You can take the boat. Just jump in when you're ready to leave.
******* '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Go as far north as you can and you'll arrive at the Hollows. Keep heading north on foot, over the rotten bridge, and you'll eventually reach an odd looking tree. That is where you'll find the Myreque.
******* {{tact|end}}
****** {{topt|I'll be back later.}}
****** '''Player:''' I'll be back later.

**** {{topt|Why do you say that this place is forsaken?}}
***** '''Player:''' Why do you say that this place is forsaken?
***** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' All of these lands are forsaken of Saradomin's kindness, only cold death from evil do we now feel.
***** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Those lucky ones to the west of the Salve little realise their fate if the river should one day become tainted.
