** {{topt|Why are they called the Myreque?}}
*** '''Player:''' Why are they called the Myreque?
*** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' It's a name the locals gave them. It means 'hidden in the myre'. Nothing fancy, it's just because that's where they hide, in Mort Myre.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Tell me about the members of the Myreque}}
*** '''Player:''' Tell me about the members of the Myreque.
*** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Well you have Radigad Ponfit. He was a mercenary from Asgarnia but he joined up with the Myreque to settle some mysterious score with the Drakans.
*** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Then there's Veliaf Hurtz, the leader of the group. He's been fighting the fight longer than any of them.
*** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Next there's Ivan Strom. He's the youngest. I hear he's an aspiring priest. Not that there's much time for that around here.
*** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' You've also got Sani Piliu, the only female of the group. She's a bit of a shady one. I reckon she was a thief before the Myreque found her.
*** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' There's Harold Evans. Used to be part of some militia but was kicked out for being too hot-headed. Now he's the main fighter for the Myreque.
*** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' Finally, you have Polmafi Ferdygris. He's the brains of the operation in many ways. Believe it or not, he used to be a scholar.
*** '''Player:''' And that's all of them?
*** '''Cyreg Paddlehorn:''' In Mort Myre it is. I sometimes hear rumour of more groups hidden in other parts of Morytania. Who knows if that's true though.
